notesStmt.note: Incipit: Veritas vim sepenumero cogitanti nichil ea plerumque facilius... (f. 1r).
Note in second hand: Questo libro sia dato ad nostro patre domino Facino de Sanctopetro in Portanova ne la perochia de Sancto Victore...(f. 64v).

msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Dialogues on ethics between Ubertus and Andreas.

supportDesc.extent: 64 leaves : 200 x 143 (126 x 94) mm. bound to 203 x 139 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, iii (contemporary paper) + 64 + i (contemporary paper); [iii], [1-64], [i]; modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 20 long lines; ruled in drypoint.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a humanistic cursive script by a single hand.

decoDesc.decoNote: 3-line blue initials with red penwork ornamentation (f. 1r, 32v); 2-line red initial with blue penwork ornamentation (f. 3r); alternating red or blue paragraph marks throughout.

history.provenance: Appears in Bernard M. Rosenthal's catalog 1 (1954), no. 33.
